<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-001-357 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 624 912</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 13 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Filemaker creators ship new product. (Attain Corp.'s In Controldesktop organizer) (Product Announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wallach, Naor.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Attain Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   In Control (Desktop accessory software) (Product introduction)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMarket EntryDesktop organizersSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****Filemaker Creators Ship New Product 12/13/91 CAMBRIDGE, MASSACHUSETTS,U.S.A., 1991 DEC 13 (NB) -- Attain Corporation is not well known in theMacintosh marketplace as of yet.andP;  No surprise there.andP;  It's a startup that isjust announcing its first product.andP;  However, the names of its founders mayring a bell in many minds.andP;  Dan Chadwick and Alan Albert previously wroteFileMaker, the very popular database manager that is now sold under theClaris label.andM;Now, they have teamed up again and produced In Control.andP;  In Control is ato-do list organizer.andP;  The special features that make In Control a bettertool than what many of us are currently using is the combination of theoutlining and spreadsheet metaphors and applying them to the mundane task ofcreating to-do lists.andM;The outline metaphor lets the user expand and collapse their lists of thingsto do based on previously described relationships.andP;  One way in which this canbe extremely useful is for detailing a set of smaller tasks that combine toform a larger task.andP;  Now you can show the list of tasks at whichever level ofdetail is most appropriate for you.andM;The Spreadsheet idea allows you to set up &quot;columns&quot; of different attributesto your to-dos.andP;  One you have created them and filled them out, you can thenselect and sort on specific attributes and prioritize your list accordingly.andO;Some attributes that you may select are: due dates, priorities, resources,etc.andM;In Control is only the first in a line of Attain products that are intendedto address the personal productivity market.andP;  According to Alan Albert, mostsoftware programs that have attempted to better organize people's lives havenot been too successful because they attempted to do too much.andP;  Attainintends to concentrate on a single task at a time and do it very, very well.andO;Then, they will let Apple's System 7 do the coordination of the tasks andthereby reap all of the benefits that have been claimed for these tools.andM;In Control is now shipping.andP;  It sells for $129.95 and most mail order houses,major distributors, and retail stores will have it.andM;(Naor Wallach/19911206/Press Contact: Alan Albert, Attain Corp.,andO;617-547-2188)</TEXT></DOC>